// React sees these as different, even though they're logically the same
// Render 1: {color: 'red'} — memory address 0x001
// Render 2: {color: 'red'} — memory address 0x002  ← different!
```

So the child component receives a "new" prop and re-renders, even though nothing actually changed.

## Solutions

**1. Lift the object outside the render (simplest)**

```jsx
